      "issue": "1964 Mustang Shelby trims are historically impossible",
      "detail": "Shelby GT350 production began in 1965, GT500 in 1967. All 1964 Shelby entries are invalid.",
      "affectedCount": 4
    },
    {
      "issue": "1964-1966 Shelby GT500 entries invalid",
      "detail": "The Shelby GT500 was not produced until 1967. Entries for 1964-1966 GT500 are historically impossible.",
      "affectedCount": 3
    },
    {
      "issue": "Modern tire sizes on classic Mustangs with 13-15\" wheels",
      "detail": "Many 1964-1978 Mustang entries show modern radial tires (215/60R17, 235/50R18, etc.) for vehicles with factory 13-15\" wheels. These are clearly inherited from wrong generation data.",
      "affectedCount": 42
    },
    {
      "issue": "Conflicting bolt patterns within same year classic Mustangs",
      "detail": "1965-1967 Mustangs show both 4x108 and 5x114.3 bolt patterns. Base cars used 4x108; 5x114.3 wasn't introduced until 1969 for big-block cars.",
      "affectedCount": 8
    }
  ],
